<ul>
<li><strong>Keep buttons visible.</strong> Donâ€™t burry your buttons where no one will ever encounter them. Unless youâ€™re giving out Cadbury Mini-Eggs, this isnâ€™t an Easter egg hunt.</li>
</ul>
<h2>2. Social Media Button Size: The Bigger the Better?</h2>
<p>Youâ€™ll find that most sites (especially those focused on virality) utilize large social share buttons. The more prominent your social share buttons are, the more likely users are to click them.</p>
<p>Large buttons can come off a bit needy, but thereâ€™s no denying that theyâ€™ll get clicked more than the smaller, more discreet buttons. The squeaky wheel gets the oil, as they say.</p>
<div style="text-align:center;"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/social-media-button-sizes.png" alt="social media button sizes" width="400" height="197" /></div>
