<h2>3. Custom Social Buttons vs. Classic Designs</h2>
<p>When taking stock of the various social sharing buttons scattered across the web, youâ€™ll notice that <strong>some sites use their own original social media button designs</strong>, while others stick to the standard, official buttons.</p>
<p>There are advantages and disadvantages to either method. <strong>Customizing your buttons can help them stand out</strong> and be a bit more eye-catching than the standard social buttons weâ€™ve all seen a trillion and one times. However, if the buttons look too foreign and unrecognizable, readers will pass right by them.</p>
<p>Let&#8217;s check out some examples of social media button variations.</p>
<p>In this example, you can see that <a href="http://www.exacttarget.com/">ExactTarget</a>, the Salesforce blog, features greyed social buttons. These desaturated grey shades go hand-in-hand with the siteâ€™s design and give an added air of professionalism.</p>
